New Blog Post! While in Norway 🇳🇴 I was honored to spend a few days deep in the arctic tundra with a Sami family who allowed me to be immersed in their lives as reindeer herders (it's not an easy job!). The winter migration cabin was an hour and a half snowmobile ride into the wilderness, had no running water, electricity was ran by a generator that had to be cranked every morning and we woke up to -25 degree Celsius temperatures ❄️ The head of the household, Nils, woke up in the wee hours every morning to tend to the herd of 700 and spent the evenings chopping firewood, smoking meat and/or fetching water from the river. But still he would go on to tell me, multiple times, that he had the best job in the world. That is passion 💛💛💛
.
Read my story about the memorable experience on the blog (link in bio) ⬆️
.
📷: In this photo Nils wife, Oddbjørg Hætta gave me the privilege to borrow her traditional gákti 🙏🏻
.
Many thanks to @VisitNatives @ImpactTravelAlliance @VisitNorway and @flynorwegian for making this trip possible 💛 #VisitNorway, #FlyNorwegian #thisissustainable

Walking down one of the cutest street in Oslo 🇳🇴 It’s lined with adorable and colorful homes (an instagrammer’s dream 😜). This is just a preview of all the great things to see and do in Norway’s capital city. There are trendy restaurants, a gorgeous opera house, a royal palace and the Oslo Fjord Sauna where you can take the icy plunge into the fjord like me! ❄️💦 Plus, in 2019 the city was named the Green Capital of the World 🌎 😮 @visitnorway @VisitOslo #VisitNorway
.
PS: I got to Oslo on a convenient and comfy flight ✈️ aboard Norwegian Air, which—by the way—was ranked as the most fuel-efficient transatlantic flight! Are you sensing a sustainability trend here?  #thisissustainable @flynorwegian  @impacttravelalliance #FlyNorwegian

These huskies were eager to run the dogsled trail as soon as we walked through the @trastiogtrine gates 🐶 They happily barked and jumped with the excitement of the anticipation. The best part was that you could tell that these pups were treated with the respect and love 💛 they deserve, which is so important when choosing a dogsledding company. #VisitNorway
.
Have you ever been dogsledding? 🐕 🛷 I’ve been before but this time was different because we got a list of our team, then had to find and harness the dogs. Plus we took turns actually being the musher!

Doing an ice plunge in the chilly Fjord is a very popular pastime in Oslo (they believe its good for circulation and the heart ❤️). And the Oslo Fjord Sauna is the perfect place to combine wellness with a bit of adventure! The idea is to sit in the sauna, a floating shed made of reclaimed driftwood and designed to overlook the beautifully architectured Opera House, until you are so hot that you can’t wait to jump into the water ❄️💦
.
I wasn’t in Norway for more than two hours before doing this jump into the fjord, though for me it was less of a jump and more of a backwards climb down the stairs—not sure which way was the better technique 😜
.
Would you take this icy plunge? .

24 hours at home zipped by before having to hop on a flight to Norway 🇳🇴 But, I’ll tell you what made the quick turnaround a whole heck of a lot easier—premium class! ✈️ .
Many people think that I always fly in luxury, but in reality that’s never the case, so partnering with @Visitnorway @impacttravelalliance and @flynorwegian to fly Norwegian Air Premium Class to Norway 🇳🇴 was a special treat. It combines budget prices with first class service and amenities.—I almost had too much leg room (is that even possible?) and the reclining chair with retractable foot rest made sleeping easy peasy 😴 (which is never the case for me in economy)! Plus, I felt very fancy to be served a drink prior to taking off. But, the BEST part was no jet lag—zilch...nada...none—because their new energy efficient planes are designed for less cabin pressure which equals less jet lag 🙏🏻 😁
